1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:02,540
(Chang)

2
00:00:02,540 --> 00:00:03,910
(Episode 110)

3
00:00:03,980 --> 00:00:04,980
Isn't this...

4
00:00:05,940 --> 00:00:07,310
Mom's necklace?

5
00:00:10,380 --> 00:00:12,520
Suk Hee's necklace is gone.

6
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:14,850
Suk Hee doesn't have a necklace.

7
00:00:15,490 --> 00:00:19,690
Then could Mom from the side dish store
be Grandfather's biological daughter?

8
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,960
That's why my mom, Chae Hwa Young, hid it.

9
00:00:23,530 --> 00:00:26,160
I can't believe Mom is
Grandfather's real daughter.

10
00:00:34,740 --> 00:00:35,740
Mom,

11
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:37,810
where did you get this necklace?

12
00:00:39,210 --> 00:00:40,750
The necklace...

13
00:00:42,180 --> 00:00:44,780
Mom has had it for a long time.

14
00:00:44,780 --> 00:00:47,150
I heard Dad kept it safe...

15
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:50,320
because it was very precious to Mom.

16
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:55,130
Maybe her parents passed it down to her
or something?

17
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:15,050
Where are you off to,
all dressed up again?

18
00:01:15,550 --> 00:01:18,520
Where I go is none of your business.

19
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:20,650
Snap out of it, will you?

20
00:01:21,150 --> 00:01:23,660
I bet you're going to meet Lee Kang Hyuk.

21
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:27,330
- You're asking for trouble.
- Why would I be?

22
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:28,390
Are you seriously asking me that?

23
00:01:28,860 --> 00:01:31,400
Don't you know what Kang Hyuk is like?

24
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,460
Kang Hyuk?

25
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:37,070
He's gentle, warm, and considerate.

26
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:40,210
He's handsome, a sharp dresser,

27
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:42,070
and a breath of fresh air.

28
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:44,640
Just thinking about him
makes me feel all warm and fuzzy.

29
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:48,510
You're insane. Han Young Ja.

30
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:51,150
Are you really planning to have an affair
with Lee Kang Hyuk?

31
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:54,390
I'm not "planning" to. I already am.

32
00:01:54,850 --> 00:01:57,360
- Han Young Ja!
- What, Kang Nam Bong?

33
00:01:57,620 --> 00:02:01,190
How much are you going to regret this?
Have you no shame before our kids?

34
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:03,600
Why are you throwing my own words
back at me?

35
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:06,100
Did your brilliant mind already forget?

36
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:10,240
- Have you forgotten what you did?
- Don't you dare talk to me like that.

37
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:12,070
Then what?
Should I call you a bastard instead?

38
00:02:12,140 --> 00:02:14,710
Hey, Han Young Ja.
Are you really going to play this dirty?

39
00:02:14,770 --> 00:02:17,240
I'm just giving you your own medicine.

40
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:20,110
Since you're the one who played dirty,
I'm just doing the same to you.

41
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:21,910
What? Is that a problem?

42
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:26,180
Oh, my.
My darling Kang Hyuk must be waiting.

43
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:33,390
Seriously, that woman has really...

44
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:38,030
lost her mind. She's crazy.

45
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:40,930
Do you think it's having any effect?

46
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,800
Well, he's definitely getting worked up.

47
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:50,070
I'm not sure
if our plan will actually work.

48
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:53,850
But at least we're giving our partners
a wake-up call.

49
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,580
As for you, Kang Hyuk,

50
00:02:56,810 --> 00:03:00,150
are you that desperate to win
Chae Hwa Young's heart...

51
00:03:00,450 --> 00:03:01,790
that you'll go on fake dates with me?

52
00:03:04,020 --> 00:03:05,160
I was just curious.

53
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:08,730
Even though you've been
by her side for so long,

54
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:12,200
I wondered if you loved her too much
to let her go.

55
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,200
She's always...

56
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:16,670
been like a mirage.

57
00:03:18,070 --> 00:03:20,370
She seems within reach,
but you can never quite catch her.

58
00:03:21,540 --> 00:03:22,710
That's part of her charm, I suppose.

59
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:24,140
What about you, Lawyer Han?

60
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:26,140
Are you trying to hold
onto Professor Kang,

61
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:27,380
even if it means using me?

62
00:03:28,950 --> 00:03:32,520
No, I have no desire
to hold on to Professor Kang.

63
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:35,290
Right now,
all I feel is the need for revenge.

64
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,660
I'm furious, and it's all so unfair.

65
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:42,590
All I want is to make him suffer
no matter what it takes.

66
00:03:43,830 --> 00:03:44,830
That's why...

67
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:49,170
I proposed this fake relationship
with you, Manager Lee.

68
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:52,400
But now that we're doing this,

69
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:57,680
Chae Hwa Young is getting wary of you.
But as for Professor Kang,

70
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,840
I'm not so sure.

71
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,350
Don't you think he might have noticed...

72
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:04,380
that we're not actually dating?

73
00:04:06,550 --> 00:04:08,150
It's not very believable, is it?

74
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,830
Should we take a selfie?

75
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,760
Gosh, sure.

76
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,730
- Okay.
- Like this?

77
00:04:20,330 --> 00:04:23,330
One, two, cheese!

78
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:24,500
Cheese!

79
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:29,870
Mom, our picnic was so much fun,
wasn't it?

80
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:32,140
We should definitely go again.

81
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:34,410
Next time, let's bring Grandpa
with us all. Okay?

82
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:35,780
Okay.

83
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,420
This is a present for Grandpa.

84
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:42,550
I'll give this to him on our picnic.

85
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:43,720
It's a four-leaf clover.

86
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:46,990
Mom put a lot of heart
into making that for Grandpa.

87
00:04:48,190 --> 00:04:50,700
I'll give this to Grandpa for you, Mom.

88
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:54,700
Mom.

89
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,040
I love you.

90
00:04:59,370 --> 00:05:01,940
Tok Hee. I love you.

91
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,840
My dear Seo Rin.

92
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:11,650
I'm sorry for everything.

93
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:15,950
My sister.

94
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:18,790
Seo Rin.

95
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,630
My little sister, Seo Rin.

96
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,260
I'm sorry, too.

97
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:26,560
As your big sister,
I feel like I only ever hurt you.

98
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:34,770
I feel like I'm finally
my mom's real daughter,

99
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,710
and I finally feel like we're twins.

100
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:39,640
We're one family.

101
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:44,320
- I love you.
- We are. We're a family.

102
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:46,150
I love you.

103
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:49,790
Shit. You're making me want to cry.

104
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,130
Grandpa.

105
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:07,170
Hey, stranger. What's the occasion?

106
00:06:09,410 --> 00:06:12,740
Grandpa, have you found Aunt Ma Eun Hye?

107
00:06:13,510 --> 00:06:14,950
Do you really have to find
your biological daughter?

108
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:17,580
- What?
- You have Oh Jang Mi and me.

109
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:19,580
We're your granddaughters.

110
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:20,820
Isn't that enough?

111
00:06:21,450 --> 00:06:24,860
- Do you really have to find her, too?
- You silly girl.

112
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,420
Are you jealous?

113
00:06:27,490 --> 00:06:29,830
Even if I do find your aunt,

114
00:06:30,430 --> 00:06:34,600
my love for you will never change.
Don't you worry.

115
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:37,740
Anyway, I'll think about it some more.

116
00:06:39,370 --> 00:06:40,370
What?

117
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:46,110
Gosh, what's gotten into her?

118
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:49,680
Seo Rin, I need to talk to you.

119
00:06:50,010 --> 00:06:52,280
Hey, that hurts! What are you doing?

120
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,450
What's gotten into you? You're hurting me!

121
00:06:59,490 --> 00:07:01,360
What's with Chae Hwa Young now?

122
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,930
They've been tense for a while.

123
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,570
Still, judging by the look on her face,

124
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:12,340
it looks like a storm's brewing.
I feel a chill in the air.

125
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:16,910
Come on!

126
00:07:17,510 --> 00:07:20,110
Don't tell me you told your grandfather
about the necklace.

127
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,910
You didn't run your mouth about me
being his real daughter, did you?

128
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,720
What's wrong? You said
you weren't his biological daughter.

129
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:27,990
- So why are you worried?
- How can I not be worried?

130
00:07:28,350 --> 00:07:31,190
His blood pressure is already high.
We have to be careful with him.

131
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,320
What if the shock is too much for him?

132
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:35,060
Mom,

133
00:07:35,460 --> 00:07:37,630
you know who Grandpa's real daughter is,
don't you?

134
00:07:37,830 --> 00:07:39,000
How would I know that?

135
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:41,500
Stop playing dumb.
You know exactly who it is.

136
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:45,900
You stole that necklace
from my mom, Jung Suk Hee.

137
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,810
- What?
- You stole that necklace...

138
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:50,110
from my mom at the side dish shop,

139
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:52,680
and I caught you comparing it
to the evidence Grandfather has.

140
00:07:53,410 --> 00:07:55,450
Are you still going to lie and deny it?

141
00:07:55,450 --> 00:07:56,550
Are you crazy?

142
00:07:56,910 --> 00:07:57,920
Shut your mouth!

143
00:07:57,980 --> 00:08:00,920
Do you think you can hide this forever?

144
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,920
All right, fine.

145
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:04,460
Let's say Jung Suk Hee is Ma Eun Hye.

146
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:07,660
Then what does that make your father,
Ma Dong Seok?

147
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:12,030
- They'd be siblings. Brother and sister.
- Shit. I know.

148
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,530
That's why I'm telling you to shut up.

149
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:18,600
A brother and sister fell in love
and had you and Oh Jang Mi.

150
00:08:18,670 --> 00:08:20,770
That's the truth of your birth.

151
00:08:20,970 --> 00:08:23,040
It's horrifying just to think about,
isn't it?

152
00:08:24,140 --> 00:08:26,010
That's why I was trying to keep it buried.

153
00:08:27,210 --> 00:08:28,210
There's no way...

154
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,150
Jung Suk Hee could be Ma Eun Hye.

155
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:34,790
I saw it with my own two eyes.
The two necklaces matched perfectly.

156
00:08:34,850 --> 00:08:36,390
Fine, let's say
Jung Suk Hee is Ma Eun Hye.

157
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:40,020
Do you think anyone
would even treat you like a human?

158
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:41,330
Mom!

159
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:46,200
The truth? Who cares about the truth?

160
00:08:46,430 --> 00:08:48,000
The moment you open your mouth,

161
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:52,940
you'll be branded the most disgusting
and grotesque person and cast out.

162
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,670
So from now on,

163
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:58,480
don't spout nonsense about necklaces
or about his biological daughter.

164
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:00,850
- Got it?
- Shit.

165
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:02,850
How could this be happening?

166
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:04,150
Seo Rin.

167
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,250
All you have to do is
keep your mouth shut.

168
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,050
Then no one will ever know.

169
00:09:08,890 --> 00:09:11,260
We can get through this
without anyone getting hurt.

170
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:13,690
All right, Seo Rin?

171
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:16,460
Darn it. Shit.

172
00:09:30,710 --> 00:09:35,110
Even if Seo Rin keeps quiet about
Dong Seok and Jung Suk Hee being siblings,

173
00:09:35,850 --> 00:09:39,280
the whole truth will come to light soon.
What do I do?

174
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:43,220
If she finds out Dong Seok was adopted,
it's all over.

175
00:09:43,290 --> 00:09:46,220
What if she secretly asks
her grandfather right now,

176
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,830
or even worse, confides in Oh Jang Mi?

177
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:51,900
What do I do?
What in the world am I supposed to do?

178
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,210
Yes, speaking.

179
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:03,670
I'm sorry, what?

180
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,440
Help me just this once, Jun Ho.

181
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:09,350
I think you're the only one
who can calm Seo Rin down.

182
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,780
Right now, Seo Rin is suspicious of me,

183
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,690
and I think she's caught on
to our shell company.

184
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:18,320
If she tells Chairman Ma about it,
or worse,

185
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:21,130
if she goes to Lawyer Kang,
we're completely finished.

186
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:22,530
Yes, I understand.

187
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,360
What would you like me to do?

188
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,360
Okay.

189
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:28,100
All right, I understand.

190
00:10:33,970 --> 00:10:35,540
What was that call about?

191
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:38,110
It's nothing.

192
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:45,820
Since his mother has no respect for me,

193
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:50,550
even my own kids treat me
like I'm invisible.

194
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:56,560
Mom?

195
00:11:14,380 --> 00:11:15,380
Seo Rin?

196
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:17,620
What is it?

197
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:20,650
Mom, my baby blanket is gone.

198
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:24,360
- Did you take it?
- Why would I take your baby blanket?

199
00:11:24,820 --> 00:11:27,320
Look again.
You probably just misplaced it.

200
00:11:27,390 --> 00:11:29,630
Shit! I'm asking because it's gone!

201
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,400
Seo Rin.
First, let's get you plastic surgery.

202
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:38,170
We'll fix your face,
and you can be born anew, Seo Rin.

203
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:39,770
Be born anew?

204
00:11:40,370 --> 00:11:43,440
How could I possibly do that right now?

205
00:11:47,380 --> 00:11:49,250
Looks like you're getting a call.
Answer it.

206
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,550
Hello, Jun Ho.

207
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,890
You're calling me first for once.
What's the occasion?

208
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,460
Are you free tomorrow?

209
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:01,060
There's something
I need to talk to you about.

210
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:04,500
Are you calling to tell me to stop
following you and bothering you again?

211
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,700
Let's go on a date.

212
00:12:07,130 --> 00:12:09,070
You want to what?

213
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,370
Go on a date.

214
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:13,600
I'll pick you up for lunch tomorrow,
so be ready.

215
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:16,640
Ma Seo Rin.

216
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:19,810
- Are you listening to me?
- Yes.

217
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:21,880
Yes, I hear you loud and clear.

218
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:25,220
Okay, I'll see you tomorrow then.

219
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:26,950
Okay.

220
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:30,350
Was that Jun Ho on the phone?

221
00:12:32,690 --> 00:12:35,660
I didn't mishear that, did I?
Jun Ho just asked me out on a date!

222
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:40,460
See? Your persistence paid off.
Jun Ho finally realized how you feel.

223
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,200
Make sure you look your best tomorrow.

224
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:45,670
Let's schedule your plastic surgery soon,
okay?

225
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:49,570
Okay. Mom, where are my pills?
Give me my pills.

226
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:52,110
Yes, I was just about to.
I brought some water for them.

227
00:12:56,910 --> 00:13:00,650
You need to take these to lose weight.
They'll make you slim and beautiful.

228
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:03,850
But these aren't addictive, are they?

229
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:07,290
Why would I give you weird medication?
I made sure it's safe.

230
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,200
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

231
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,410
- This smells so good.
- It does, doesn't it?

232
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,880
What?

233
00:13:25,310 --> 00:13:28,310
- Hey. Tok Hee's here.
- Goodness!

234
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:29,850
Seo Rin's here.

235
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:32,950
Seo Rin, what brings you here
so early in the morning?

236
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:38,120
I have a date with Jun Ho later,
so I won't have time to stop by then.

237
00:13:38,190 --> 00:13:39,420
A date with Jun Ho?

238
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,290
That's great, Seo Rin.

239
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,530
Here.

240
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:45,730
The evidence I've collected.

241
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,270
Seo Rin...

242
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,570
Actually, I found this a while ago.

243
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,770
I was hesitant
because of my mom, Chae Hwa Young.

244
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:57,510
Now that we've made up, Oh Jang Mi,
consider it a reconciliation gift.

245
00:13:57,780 --> 00:13:58,810
Seo Rin...

246
00:14:00,880 --> 00:14:04,180
- I'm sorry.
- What are you sorry for?

247
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,450
- The truth is...
- Seo Rin.

248
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,590
We've already made a copy...

249
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,760
of the evidence on that USB drive.

250
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,160
What? How?

251
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:18,230
Geum Soon found it while cleaning
and gave it to me.

252
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:20,730
I made a copy of it...

253
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:23,570
and then put it back on your vanity
without you knowing.

254
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:26,600
I'm sorry I wasn't honest with you.

255
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,210
Shit. When did you
have the time to copy that?

256
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:32,010
Looks like you got a little smarter.

257
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:34,980
Mom.

258
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,910
Here, try this on.

259
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:38,420
It's a gift.

260
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:41,650
What? A present for Suk Hee!

261
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:47,190
You're so lucky, Mom. Go on, try it on.

262
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,470
It looks amazing on you.

263
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:05,780
- Suk Hee has a new outfit! I love it.
- It's colorful and fits you so perfectly.

264
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:08,280
Mom really loves it.

265
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:09,650
Thanks, Seo Rin.

266
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:14,180
To celebrate your new outfit,
let me take a picture.

267
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,190
- Yes!
- That's a great idea.

268
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,490
One, two, three.

269
00:15:35,170 --> 00:15:36,210
What's all this?

270
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:39,280
You have a date with Jun Ho.
You need to dress to impress.

271
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,650
I just spoke with Jun Ho,

272
00:15:41,950 --> 00:15:43,480
and it sounds like
he's pretty excited too.

273
00:15:45,020 --> 00:15:46,020
Really?

274
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:47,790
Of course.

275
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:50,390
I picked out some clothes and accessories,

276
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:51,920
all in the style Jun Ho likes for you.
Take a look.

277
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:57,560
But Jang Mi already picked out an outfit
for me to congratulate me on the date.

278
00:15:57,630 --> 00:16:00,660
Wear this one. I told you,
I chose it specifically for his taste.

279
00:16:01,570 --> 00:16:04,340
It's your first date,
so you have to sweep him off his feet.

280
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:07,070
Thanks, Mom.

281
00:16:07,540 --> 00:16:11,410
Go knock him dead.
Then the wedding will happen in a flash.

282
00:16:12,140 --> 00:16:13,140
Right.

283
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:17,550
What's this?

284
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:20,480
Right. Before I send you off,

285
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:23,320
this is my final gift to you as a mother,
Ma Seo Rin.

286
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:26,460
At least for the sake of the 30 years
I spent raising you,

287
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,560
this is the least I can do.

288
00:16:38,140 --> 00:16:39,440
You look a little different today.

289
00:16:41,070 --> 00:16:43,370
Do I look okay?

290
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:45,640
Yes, you look great.

291
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:53,220
Thank you.

292
00:16:57,050 --> 00:16:59,620
What did you think of the restaurant
I took you to?

293
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:03,990
It was an excellent choice.
The food was amazing.

294
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:08,200
You must have great taste in restaurants
because you're a chef.

295
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,400
I'm glad to hear that.

296
00:17:11,070 --> 00:17:12,500
After all, today is a special day.

297
00:17:15,570 --> 00:17:18,440
But can I ask you something?

298
00:17:18,910 --> 00:17:20,110
Of course. Anything.

299
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:22,610
Why the sudden change of heart?

300
00:17:25,550 --> 00:17:26,620
A change of heart?

301
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:31,690
Let's just say I wanted
to get to know you, Seo Rin.

302
00:17:34,090 --> 00:17:36,390
So you're saying you're interested in me.

303
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:38,130
Thank you.

304
00:17:41,530 --> 00:17:42,530
Seo Rin.

305
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:44,440
Yes?

306
00:17:44,970 --> 00:17:47,140
Don't take this the wrong way,

307
00:17:48,010 --> 00:17:49,170
but I think...

308
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:51,040
you should get the facial surgery.

309
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:54,450
That way, I can date an even prettier you.

310
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:57,780
You used to be so cute and pretty.

311
00:17:58,880 --> 00:18:00,920
Are you saying I'm not pretty now?

312
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:04,190
- Because of my scar?
- If we're considering marriage,

313
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:06,290
it's something I have to be sure about.

314
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,430
- Marriage?
- A senior colleague recently told me...

315
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:15,100
about a doctor at a hospital out of town
who's incredible at facial reconstruction.

316
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:18,600
Apparently, he's one of the top surgeons
in the country skill-wise,

317
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:20,940
but he hates the hassle and fame
that come with it,

318
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,610
so he purposely works at a hospital
out of the way.

319
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:28,280
- Is there really someone like that?
- Yes. I looked into it, and it's true.

320
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:32,550
Did you look all this up
just for me, Jun Ho?

321
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:35,650
I'd much rather date a pretty girl,
you know.

322
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:41,730
Please, Jun Ho.

323
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:45,660
Seo Rin might not want to go
if she hears the hospital's out of town.

324
00:18:46,030 --> 00:18:48,570
Jun Ho, you have to be the one
to convince her.

325
00:18:49,130 --> 00:18:50,970
She'll listen to you.

326
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:52,440
Why should I have to do that?

327
00:18:52,570 --> 00:18:54,710
It's to get Seo Rin on our side.

328
00:18:55,170 --> 00:18:57,310
Once we have Seo Rin on our side,

329
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,410
our business venture can move forward
without a hitch.

330
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:03,310
What does plastic surgery have to do
with any of that?

331
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:04,680
You don't understand women.

332
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:08,090
If we make sure Seo Rin's surgery
is a success...

333
00:19:08,390 --> 00:19:09,890
and make her feel beautiful again,

334
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:14,290
she'll open up to us
and be on our side in a heartbeat.

335
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:18,760
So please,
just convince her for me, Jun Ho.

336
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:29,310
So I'd like you to get the surgery
as soon as possible.

337
00:19:29,740 --> 00:19:30,740
Okay.

338
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:33,610
Even if you hadn't said anything,

339
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,710
I was already planning
to get the surgery soon.

340
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,250
Jun Ho.

341
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:46,790
Today is the best day of my life.

342
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:50,390
I'm so happy, and it's all thanks to you.

343
00:19:51,160 --> 00:19:52,860
I feel hopeful about the future again.

344
00:19:54,130 --> 00:19:55,130
Thank you.

345
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:01,100
I'm sorry, Seo Rin.

346
00:20:01,770 --> 00:20:03,810
I don't know if I'm doing the right thing.

347
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:07,140
But as important as love is to me,

348
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,610
I can't just ignore my ambition.

349
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:13,180
This is where my sympathy for you ends.

350
00:20:24,530 --> 00:20:25,730
You're back.

351
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:27,800
Did you have fun on your date?

352
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:30,670
Yes. It was the best day ever.

353
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:34,770
Mom, I want to get
the facial surgery right away.

354
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:38,340
Really? Then I'll start looking into it
for you right away.

355
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:41,350
No, it's okay.
Jun Ho has already found a hospital.

356
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:44,380
Call Jun Ho
and schedule it right away, Mom.

357
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:47,620
He did?
Jun Ho even found a hospital for you?

358
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:49,590
- Yes.
- That's something.

359
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:53,790
He said he wasn't interested in you,
but I guess that was just for show.

360
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:03,000
(Sil)

361
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,510
My dear child.

362
00:21:10,340 --> 00:21:11,710
Where are you?

363
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:33,530
Why do you suddenly want to see
your father's belongings?

364
00:21:34,630 --> 00:21:35,830
I was just thinking,

365
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,600
I don't think I've ever really looked
at Dad's belongings.

366
00:21:39,970 --> 00:21:41,240
I've been so thoughtless, haven't I?

367
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:44,010
What's this stain?

368
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,510
Oh, that...

369
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:48,380
That's the handkerchief
your father, Dong Seok,

370
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:51,420
kept by his chest on his first day
of elementary school.

371
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:54,950
But wouldn't you know it,
he got a nosebleed that day,

372
00:21:55,090 --> 00:21:56,790
and some of it got on the handkerchief.

373
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,060
Really?

374
00:21:59,990 --> 00:22:03,030
Grandfather, I'm going to hold on to this.

375
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,960
If this is a bloodstain,

376
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,130
Dad's DNA must still be on it.

377
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:25,280
No matter how I think about it,

378
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:28,150
there's no way Mom and Dad
could be siblings.

379
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:32,090
I'll run a DNA test with this
and my mom at the side dish store...

380
00:22:32,520 --> 00:22:33,920
to find out for sure.

381
00:22:35,830 --> 00:22:37,590
Why can't I tell anyone?

382
00:22:38,130 --> 00:22:41,570
Your grandfather might not let you go
if he learns it's a hospital out of town.

383
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:45,200
We've already booked the appointment,
and that would cause a lot of trouble.

384
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:48,810
If we cancel, we'll have to wait
two years for another opening.

385
00:22:50,570 --> 00:22:53,310
Today's the last day I'll have this face.

386
00:22:55,110 --> 00:22:58,180
By the way, have you been taking
the diet pills I gave you?

387
00:22:58,550 --> 00:23:01,890
Maybe that's why.
You look like you've lost some weight,

388
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:03,690
and your figure seems more toned.

389
00:23:03,850 --> 00:23:06,320
Of course.
I've been paying extra attention to it.

390
00:23:06,460 --> 00:23:08,060
I just have to take care of my face now.

391
00:23:09,030 --> 00:23:10,030
By the way, Seo Rin,

392
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,830
you trust me, right?

393
00:23:15,170 --> 00:23:16,700
Why are you asking me that
all of a sudden?

394
00:23:17,030 --> 00:23:18,500
It's just that...

395
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:21,440
after I kidnapped you,

396
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:24,510
I accidentally ruined your face
in that accident.

397
00:23:26,210 --> 00:23:27,780
I was worried
you might still resent me for it.

398
00:23:28,550 --> 00:23:31,250
To this day, it's my biggest regret.

399
00:23:32,050 --> 00:23:35,090
If I could turn back time,
I would do things differently.

400
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:37,350
I'm so sorry, Seo Rin.

401
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:41,060
I'll admit my feelings
were all over the place,

402
00:23:42,060 --> 00:23:43,130
but not anymore.

403
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:46,800
I trust you now, Mom,
because Jun Ho is with me now.

404
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:49,370
Good.

405
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:53,340
Anyway, you have your surgery tomorrow,
so you should get to bed early.

406
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:07,520
Goodness, you've been
going out a lot lately, Seo Rin.

407
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:09,950
Are you really dating someone these days?

408
00:24:10,020 --> 00:24:13,820
But she does seem to have brightened up
since she's been getting out more.

409
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:16,190
It's time for me to go back to Dream.

410
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:19,900
That's why I'm meeting people
and going to galleries and things.

411
00:24:20,930 --> 00:24:23,470
Of course. You're doing the right thing,
my sweet girl.

412
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,770
- Grandfather.
- Goodness.

413
00:24:26,770 --> 00:24:29,710
Don't you worry. Your sweet girl, Seo Rin,

414
00:24:29,810 --> 00:24:32,540
is going to live a long, long life
taking care of you.

415
00:24:32,910 --> 00:24:35,010
So you need to stay healthy, too.

416
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:38,780
Where are you off to, dressed so casually?
Working out? A date?

417
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,180
None of your business.

418
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:44,350
I'm off!
You're all in for a huge surprise today.

419
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:46,590
Hey, what is it?

420
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,860
Goodbye, everybody!

421
00:24:53,730 --> 00:24:55,800
That girl...

422
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,130
She seems to be in a good mood
for a change.

423
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:05,210
(Ohjeong Plastic Surgery)

424
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,590
Mom.

425
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:24,460
I'm shaking, and I'm cold.

426
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:26,260
It's okay.

427
00:25:26,730 --> 00:25:28,470
You won't feel a thing
once the anesthesia kicks in.

428
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:33,840
You'll wake up prettier than Oh Jang Mi,
so don't you worry.

429
00:25:34,370 --> 00:25:37,340
You'll be the Ma Seo Rin you used to be,
so just hang in there.

430
00:25:38,010 --> 00:25:41,610
But why am I so scared?

431
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:48,990
I'm right here.
There's nothing to be scared of.

432
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:53,390
Mom, I don't think I can do this.

433
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,630
I'd rather do this another time.

434
00:25:55,630 --> 00:25:58,360
Do you know how hard it was to get this?

435
00:25:59,130 --> 00:26:00,860
After some sleep,

436
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:03,400
you'll wake up
as a completely different person.

437
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:04,600
So you don’t have to worry.

438
00:26:29,230 --> 00:26:31,930
Did Seo Rin enjoy her date with Jun Ho?

439
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,600
Yes, she's so happy.

440
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:37,230
But don't you think
it's a little strange...

441
00:26:37,230 --> 00:26:39,870
that Jun Ho suddenly
went on a date with Seo Rin?

442
00:26:41,170 --> 00:26:42,170
I'm not sure.

443
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:47,980
What is it, Jang Mi?

444
00:26:48,780 --> 00:26:49,980
It's just...

445
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:53,350
Baek Ho. I'm scared.

446
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:55,350
Why am I so scared all of a sudden?

447
00:26:56,250 --> 00:26:59,360
Are you okay?
Try to take some deep breaths.

448
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:02,090
Jang Mi.

449
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:03,830
Breathe.

450
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:34,860
I'm so scared.

451
00:27:35,690 --> 00:27:36,690
Help me.

452
00:27:37,590 --> 00:27:38,600
Jang Mi.

453
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:40,500
Mom.

454
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,400
Seo Rin.

455
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:49,510
Thank you for being my daughter
all this time.

456
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:52,980
Now, you can rest in peace.

457
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:55,010
What...

458
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:56,650
What does that mean?

459
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:59,050
Are you trying to kill me, Mom?

460
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:00,750
This can't be happening.

461
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:02,750
Chae Hwa Young!

462
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,450
(The First Man)

463
00:28:36,620 --> 00:28:40,090
The death certificate and funeral
must be under Oh Jang Mi's name.

464
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:42,660
It's the one way
to save your granddaughter, Seo Rin,

465
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,760
and Dream Hotel's reputation, Father.

466
00:28:44,930 --> 00:28:47,730
You're the one who made Jang Mi die,
didn't you?

467
00:28:47,730 --> 00:28:48,800
I'm warning you.

468
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:51,670
I won't let you or Chae Hwa Young
get away with this.

469
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:55,670
It's my fault Tok Hee died.

470
00:28:55,940 --> 00:28:57,470
You killed her!

471
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:00,380
I'm going to rip you to shreds!

472
00:29:00,380 --> 00:29:03,010
I'll kill you! Chae Hwa Young

473
00:29:04,010 --> 00:29:05,980
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
